# Linear traceability (agents)

You do **not** need a branch like `firstname/n43-351-slug` for Linear to stay accurate, **if** commits carry the issue in the message.

## When creating commits

- Prefer **`/git/commit`** (or follow the same steps in [`commands/git/commit.md`](../commands/git/commit.md)).
- On **personal branches** (no `TEAM-123` in the branch name), **always** complete [Step 1b — resolve primary issue](../commands/git/commit.md#1b-resolve-primary-linear-issue), then [4f-linear-footer-inject](../commands/git/commit.md#4f-linear-footer-inject) so the footer includes **`Refs N43-XXX`** (or `Closes` / `Fixes` / `Resolves` when appropriate).
- If the user works on a stable personal branch (e.g. `colin`), add to **repo root `AGENTS.md`**:

  ```text
  defaultLinearIssue: N43-351
  ```

  (Adjust team key and id.) Agents use this when the branch has no issue id and the user did not name one in chat.

## After raw `git commit` / `git push`

- Follow [linear-sync.mdc](./linear-sync.mdc) and [`/git/push` §4b](../commands/git/push.md#4b-primary-issue-branch--tip-commit--agents) for **primary** resolution from branch → tip commit footer → `AGENTS.md`.

## Human preference

Branch-per-issue remains fine for humans; this rule makes **agents** responsible for footers and primary resolution so `/git/push` batch sync stays correct without renaming branches.
